    <insight>
        <p>
            The increase in value of an asset over time is referred to as <term>Appreciation</term>.
        </p>
        <p>
            Let the original value of the land be <m>P</m>, the new value be <m>A</m>, the increase in value be <m>I</m>, and the percentage increase be <m>R</m>. 
        </p>
        <p>
            From the learner experience, we can see that,
        </p>
        <p>
            <md>
                <mrow> A = \amp \; P + I </mrow>
                <mrow> I = \amp \; \frac{R}{100} \times P </mrow>
                <mrow> A = \amp \; P + \frac{R}{100} \times P </mrow>
                <mrow> = \amp \; P \left(1 + \frac{R}{100}\right) </mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
        <p>
            For the second year the new value becomes the original value.
        </p>
        <p>
            <md>
                <mrow> A = \amp \; P \left(1 + \frac{R}{100}\right) + \frac{R}{100} \times P \left(1 + \frac{R}{100}\right) </mrow>
                <mrow> = \amp \; P \left(1 + \frac{R}{100}\right) \left(1 + \frac{R}{100}\right) </mrow>
                <mrow> = \amp \; P \left(1 + \frac{R}{100}\right)^2 </mrow>
            </md>
            
        </p>
            <p>
                In general, after <m>T</m> years, the value of the asset can be calculated using the formula, <me>A = P \left(1 + \frac{R}{100}\right)^T</me>
            </p> 
    </insight>

    <!-- Add further instruction (not in a block) to develop ideas as needed -->

    <xi:include href="../lesson-plan-templates/example-intro.ptx" />

    <!-- Add at least 3 examples -->

    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A piece of land in a developing suburban area is purchased for <m>2,500,000</m> Shillings. If the value of land in that area appreciates at a steady rate of <m>15\%</m> per annum, what will be the value of the land after <m>6</m> years?
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <alert>Identify the given values</alert>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> P \amp =\; 2,500,000 \;\ text{shillings} </mrow>
                    <mrow> R \amp = \; 15 \% </mrow>
                    <mrow> T \amp = \;  6\;\text{years}</mrow>
                    <mrow> A \amp = \; ? </mrow>
                </md>
                
            </p>
            <p>
                Apply the Appreciation formula, <m> A = P(1 + R)^T</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> A \amp =\; 2,500,000 (1 + \frac{15}{100})^6 </mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp = \;2,500,000 \times 2.31306 = 5,782,650 \text{ Shillings}</mrow>
                </md>
                
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A company's currently valued is <m>4,200,000</m> Shillings. It has been appreciating at a rate of <m>8 \%</m> per year for the last <m>5</m> years. How much was the original value?
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> A \amp =\; 4,200,000 \;\ text{shillings} </mrow>
                    <mrow> R \amp = \; 8 \% \;\text{P.A}</mrow>
                    <mrow> T \amp = \;  5\;\text{years}</mrow>
                    <mrow> P \amp = \; ?</mrow>
                </md>
                
            </p>
            <p>
                Making <m>P</m> the subject in the appreciation formula, <m> P = \frac{A}{1 + \frac{R}{100}^T}</m> 
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> P \amp = \; 4,200,000</mrow>
                </md>
                
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A house was bought for <m>120,000</m> Shillings and sold <m>10</m> years later for <m>311,200</m> Shillings. At what annual rate did the house appreciate?
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                From the appreciation formula 
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> R \amp = \; 100 \times \left( \sqrt[T]{\frac{A}{P}} - 1\right)</mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp = \; 100 \times \left(\sqrt[10]{\frac{311,200}{120,000}} - 1\right)</mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp = \; 10 \% </mrow>
                </md>
                
            </p>
        </answer>
    </example>

